uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data

Class DiffParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data.DumpParser
      • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data.DiffParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.xml.sax.ContentHandler, Contexed

    public class DiffParser
extends DumpParser
    A DumpParser that looks for existing records unchanged from an initial baseline dump and marks them as seen in an enclosed Dumper so they will be excluded from a subsequently generated dump generated by this Dumper. This dump will therefore only contain the entries needed to update the baseline state to the new state.

    The dump being compared against should ideally be a newly generated dump from an earlier state of the same database as this code cannot work out the correct id to use if the record has changed and has to use the id from the parse. Note this relies on Record#findDuplicate(int) to determine if a record is unchanged.

    spb
